  "prompt": "Does Cyanogen 13.1 on Moto G3 support VOLTE? If yes, how can I turn on?",
  "response": "CyanogenMod, particularly version 13.1, was a popular custom ROM based on Android Marshmallow. While it brought many enhancements and features, support for VoLTE (Voice over LTE) largely depended on the specific device and carrier compatibility.\n\nFor the Moto G3, VoLTE support with CyanogenMod 13.1 may not be guaranteed, as VoLTE functionality often requires specific firmware and carrier configurations that are typically found in stock ROMs. However, you can check if VoLTE is available and attempt to enable it using the following steps:\n\n1. **Check VoLTE compatibility:**\n   Ensure your carrier supports VoLTE and has provisioned your SIM for VoLTE.\n\n2. **Access Phone Info:**\n   - Go to your device's dialer.\n   - Dial `*#*#4636#*#*` to access the testing menu.\n   - Select \"Phone information.\"\n\n3. **Enable VoLTE:**\n   - In the Phone information menu, look for an option related to \"VoLTE Provisioned\" or \"IMS Service.\"\n   - Toggle the \"VoLTE Provisioned\" switch to enable it if available.\n   - Restart your device.\n\n4. **Check Network settings:**\n   - Go to `Settings > More > Cellular networks`.\n   - Look for an option to enable VoLTE or Enhanced 4G LTE Mode.\n\nIf these options are not available or VoLTE does not work, it is likely that CyanogenMod 13.1 does not support VoLTE on the Moto G3 due to hardware or firmware limitations. In this case, you might need to revert to the stock ROM provided by Motorola, which may have better support for carrier-specific features like VoLTE.\n\nFor a more modern alternative, you can also check if LineageOS (the successor to CyanogenMod) has better support for VoLTE on the Moto G3, as newer versions might offer improved compatibility and features.",
